5C%22%20height%3D%5C%228256%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECatherine%20Goetze%20turned%20an%20old%20rotary%20phone%20into%20a%20bluetooth%20device%20that%20connects%20to%20her%20cell%20phone.%3Cp%3EYasara%20Gunawardena%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETiffany%20Ng%2C%20a%2024-year-old%20tech%20and%20culture%20writer%20based%20in%20New%20York%2C%20was%20too%20attached%20to%20her%20iPhone%2C%20so%20she%20did%20what%20humans%20do%20when%20trying%20to%20tame%20an%20unruly%20beast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20chained%20it%20to%20a%20wall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENg%20felt%20she%20was%20spending%20too%20much%20time%20staring%20at%20her%20little%20screen%20and%20wanted%20an%20escape.%20Turns%20out%20she's%20in%20good%20company.%20Over%2040%25%20of%20American%20adults%20%E2%80%94%20and%2062%25%20of%20those%20under%2030%20%E2%80%94%20say%20they%20are%20on%20their%20phones%20%26quot%3Balmost%20constantly%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Finternet%2F2024%2F01%2F31%2Famericans-use-of-mobile-technology-and-home-broadband%2Fpi_2024-01-24_mobile-broadband_0-05-png%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPew%20Research%3C%2Fa%3E%20survey%20conducted%20in%20late%202023.%20Most%20Americans%2C%20including%2081%25%20of%20adults%20under%2030%2C%20believe%20they%20use%20their%20phone%20too%20much%2C%20a%202022%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F393785%2Famericans-close-wary-bond-smartphone.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGallup%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENg's%20desire%20to%20turn%20the%20supercomputer%20in%20her%20pocket%20into%20a%20makeshift%20landline%20is%20also%20one%20that's%20shared%20by%20other%20zoomers%20and%20millennials.%20Some%20Americans%20are%20going%20full%20Luddite%2C%20giving%20up%20smartphones%20altogether%20in%20favor%20of%20so-called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fappstinence-movement-tech-lovers-dumping-smartphones-age-of-dumb-phones-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edumb%20phones%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20some%20parents%20are%20easing%20their%20kids%20into%20technology%20by%20opting%20for%20classic%20landlines%20instead%20of%20iPhones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20plenty%20of%20people%20who%20want%20a%20break%20from%20their%20screens%20but%20aren't%20quite%20ready%20or%20able%20to%20ditch%20the%20conveniences%20of%20modern%20technology%20altogether.%20So%20instead%20of%20giving%20up%20their%20smartphones%2C%20some%20young%20people%20are%20creating%20setups%20that%20mimic%20landlines%20%E2%80%94%20by%20chaining%20their%20phone%20to%20the%20wall%20or%20creating%20a%20wall%20mount%20to%20%26quot%3Bhang%20up%20the%20phone%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20carry%20it%20with%20them%20all%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Maddie%20DeVico's%20phone%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e95f425dbc4fd10daaa8a1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225399%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESome%20young%20people%20are%20trying%20to%20bring%20back%20%26quot%3Bhanging%20up%26quot%3B%20the%20phone.%3Cp%3EAmanda%20Lopez%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EYalda%20Uhls%2C%20a%20research%20psychologist%20and%20the%20founding%20CEO%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20Scholars%20and%20Storytellers%20at%20UCLA%2C%20said%20studies%20have%20shown%20that%20creating%20physical%20distance%20between%20yourself%20and%20your%20phone%20can%20make%20a%20big%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhbr.org%2F2018%2F03%2Fhaving-your-smartphone-nearby-takes-a-toll-on-your-thinking%3Futm_source%3Dchatgpt.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20measured%20how%20participants%20completed%20tasks%20when%20they%20had%20their%20phones%20face%20down%20on%20their%20desk%2C%20in%20their%20pocket%20or%20a%20nearby%20bag%2C%20or%20in%20another%20room.%20The%20people%20who%20had%20their%20phones%20in%20another%20room%20performed%20the%20best.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20can%20see%20your%20phone%2C%20if%20you%20can%20grab%20it%20and%20walk%20around%20with%20it%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20want%20to%20do%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIf%20it's%20separate%20from%20you%2C%20that's%20the%20only%20time%20people%20stop%20really%20thinking%20about%20their%20phone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20talked%20to%20three%20young%20adults%20who%20said%20creating%20a%20physical%20boundary%20around%20their%20phone%20has%20drastically%20improved%20their%20screen%20time%20and%20their%20quality%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226a97622b-0e88-4b3f-866f-3b7d3850a213%5C%22%3EBring%20back%20hanging%20up%20the%20phone%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMaddie%20DeVico%2C%20a%2031-year-old%20who%20works%20in%20sales%20for%20a%20software%20company%20in%20Denver%2C%20said%20she%20was%20feeling%20overwhelmed%20by%20her%20reliance%20on%20technology%20and%20trapped%20by%20the%20constant%20need%20to%20respond%20to%20messages%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20romanticized%20the%20landline%20she%20had%20during%20her%20childhood%20in%20New%20Jersey%20and%20became%20obsessed%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20getting%20back%20to%20%26quot%3Bhanging%20up%20the%20phone%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20turning%20her%20device%20into%20something%20that%20she%20set%20down%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20workday%20rather%20than%20carry%20with%20her%20constantly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20she%20took%20some%20leftover%20clay%20and%20made%20her%20own%20phone%20docking%20station.%20She%20hung%20it%20on%20her%20wall%20near%20her%20kitchen%20and%20started%20setting%20her%20phone%20there%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20workday.%20Initially%2C%20she%20noticed%20she%20would%20go%20back%20to%20it%20and%20pick%20it%20up%20to%20scroll%2C%20but%20after%20a%20brief%20transition%20period%2C%20she%20found%20herself%20setting%20it%20down%20and%20not%20picking%20it%20up%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%2211216%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Maddie%20DeVico%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e969601c1f80efbec567a1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%228256%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMaddie%20DeVico%20made%20her%20own%20phone%20dock%20that%20she%20could%20hang%20her%20phone%20up%20on.%3Cp%3EAmanda%20Lopez%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20I%20started%20doing%20that%2C%20putting%20my%20phone%20away%2C%20I%20just%20stopped%20reaching%20for%20it%20all%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20DeVico%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20just%20noticed%20this%20mental%20freeness%20that%20came%20with%20disconnecting.%20It%20was%20kind%20of%20a%20crazy%20shift.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20her%20screen%20time%20went%20down%20by%20three%20hours%20each%20day.%20Her%20friends%20learned%20that%20they%20were%20no%20longer%20going%20to%20get%20an%20immediate%20text%20back%20from%20her%2C%20and%20she%20even%20started%20leaving%20the%20phone%20in%20its%20dock%20when%20she%20left%20the%20house.%20She%20suddenly%20had%20more%20time%20to%20do%20other%20things%2C%20like%20cooking%20and%20crafting.%20She%20started%20spending%20more%20time%20in%20her%20garden%20just%20looking%20at%20bugs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20so%20shocked%20with%20the%20amount%20of%20stress%20that%20left%20my%20body.%20It%20was%20life-changing%20in%20a%20way%20because%20I%20ran%20a%20little%20anxious%20before%20I%20started%20this%20habit%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20her%20friends%20come%20over%20for%20dinner%2C%20she%20also%20has%20them%20keep%20their%20phones%20away%20from%20the%20table%2C%20and%20as%20a%20result%2C%20she%20said%20they're%20having%20more%20meaningful%20discussions%20about%20personal%20topics.%20After%20she%20posted%20about%20the%20phone%20dock%20on%20TikTok%2C%20she%20racked%20up%20nearly%20a%20million%20views%20and%20heard%20from%20hundreds%20of%20others%20about%20how%20they%2C%20too%2C%20are%20trying%20to%20bring%20back%20hanging%20up%20the%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20we're%20just%20really%20genuinely%20trying%20to%20go%20back%20to%20living%20simpler%20without%20the%20chaos%20and%20without%20all%20the%20distractions%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2252e1cd02-df3e-4fd8-9fa3-8f305f7e5929%5C%22%3EA%20thirst%20for%20old-school%20tech%20and%20'simpler%20times'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUhls%2C%20the%20UCLA%20researcher%20who%20often%20works%20with%20members%20of%20Gen%20Z%20and%20Gen%20Alpha%2C%20said%20young%20people%20are%20acutely%20aware%20of%20how%20much%20time%20they%20spend%20on%20their%20phones%2C%20and%20often%20make%20efforts%20to%20spend%20less%20time%20on%20them.%20She%20said%20even%20though%20they%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20on%20social%20media%2C%20they%20recognize%20that%20it's%20not%20particularly%20deep%20or%20fulfilling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20craving%20connections%20and%20craving%20more%20meaningful%20experiences%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20so%20desperate%20for%20connection%20that%20they've%20embraced%20the%20Luddite%20movement.%20At%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanti-tech-rally-apple-iphone-elon-musk-tesla-luddite-movement-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanti-technology%20rally%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20New%20York%20City%20last%20month%2C%20dozens%20of%20young%20people%20put%20Apple%20on%20a%20mock%20trial%20and%20smashed%20iPhones.%20Others%20are%20embracing%20%26quot%3Bappstinence%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20term%20coined%20by%20a%2024-year-old%20grad%20student%20at%20Harvard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChaining%20her%20phone%20to%20a%20wall%20was%20one%20of%20several%20experiments%20Ng%20has%20done%20as%20part%20of%20her%20newsletter%2C%20Cyber%20Celibate%2C%20which%20she%20uses%20to%20explore%20our%20relationship%20with%20technology.%20She's%20also%20printed%20out%20her%20TikTok%20%26quot%3BFor%20You%26quot%3B%20page%20to%20read%20like%20a%20newspaper%20and%20sent%20carrier%20pigeons%20instead%20of%20texts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tiffany%20Ng%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e962a8cc993f9955d00251%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETiffany%20Ng%20chained%20her%20phone%20to%20the%20wall%20using%20a%20belt.%3Cp%3ETiffany%20Ng%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20chain%20to%20the%20wall%20experiment%2C%20Ng%20gave%20her%20phone%20a%20full%20charge%2C%20unplugged%20it%2C%20and%20then%20put%20it%20on%20its%20leash%20by%20making%20creative%20use%20of%20a%20chain%20link%20belt.%20She%20was%20committed%20to%20leaving%20it%20there%2C%20even%20when%20she%20left%20the%20house%2C%20and%20not%20giving%20it%20another%20charge%20for%20a%20full%20week.%20She%20put%20a%20bench%20in%20front%20of%20it%2C%20where%20she%20could%20sit%20when%20she%20needed%20to%20use%20her%20phone%2C%20but%20that%20wasn't%20comfy%20enough%20to%20make%20an%20endless%20scroll%20session%20appealing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20couple%20of%20days%2C%20Ng%20said%20she%20would%20look%20forward%20to%20going%20home%20and%20being%20able%20to%20scroll%20on%20her%20phone.%20But%20when%20she%20finally%20opened%20her%20special%20media%20feed%2C%20that%20excitement%20was%20met%20with%20the%20%26quot%3Bvery%20anti-climactic%20experience%20of%20looking%20at%20pictures%20of%20Alix%20Earle%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20influencer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20almost%20religious%20experience%20of%20being%20on%20your%20phone%20kind%20of%20loses%20its%20aura%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20alluring%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20satisfying%20at%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20surprising%20things%20she%20found%20was%20how%20%26quot%3Bout%20of%20sight%2C%20out%20of%20mind%26quot%3B%20her%20phone%20really%20was.%20When%20she%20met%20up%20with%20friends%20in%20the%20park%2C%20worked%20from%20a%20coffee%20shop%2C%20or%20even%20just%20during%20her%20commute%2C%20she%20didn't%20find%20herself%20reaching%20for%20her%20phone%20the%20way%20she%20expected%20to.%20Instead%2C%20she%20started%20to%20notice%20her%20surroundings%20%E2%80%94%20like%20the%20buildings%20around%20the%20train%20station%20she%20frequents%20or%20how%20people%20act%20differently%20on%20the%20L%20train%20versus%20the%202.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20to%20sound%20overdramatic%2C%20but%20toward%20the%20end%2C%20it%20really%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20reentering%20real%20life%20in%20a%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Ng%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENg%20said%20she%20thinks%20Gen%20Z%20is%20pining%20for%20simpler%20technology%20and%20simpler%20times%20(she%20recently%20was%20delighted%20to%20learn%20what%20dial-up%20internet%20was).%20While%20the%20experiment%20lasted%20a%20week%2C%20she%20still%20continues%20to%20actively%20leave%20her%20phone%20in%20another%20room%2C%20or%20even%20leave%20it%20behind%20when%20she%20gets%20out%20of%20the%20house%2C%20somewhere%20close%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225ef096d4-6b55-4b93-9359-2c58b9f6d169%5C%22%3EBest%20of%20both%20worlds%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everyone%20romanticizing%20the%20days%20of%20the%20landline%20is%20against%20modern%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECatherine%20Goetze%20is%20the%20creator%20of%20CatGPT%2C%20an%20online%20media%20brand%20focused%20on%20AI%20education.%20The%20millennial%20content%20creator%20worked%20in%20tech%20before%20amassing%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20followers%20with%20helpful%20videos%20intended%20to%20make%20AI%20more%20accessible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Goetze%20also%20had%20a%20desire%20to%20be%20reachable%20without%20being%20tethered%20to%20her%20smartphone.%20So%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20ago%2C%20she%20bought%20an%20old%20rotary%20phone%20and%20some%20special%20parts%20and%20turned%20it%20into%20a%20Bluetooth%20device%20connected%20to%20her%20cellphone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20someone%20called%20her%20cellphone%2C%20her%20%26quot%3Blandline%26quot%3B%20rang%2C%20so%20she%20could%20be%20alerted%20to%20incoming%20calls%20without%20also%20having%20to%20be%20open%20to%20every%20other%20potential%20phone%20notification.%20She%20could%20also%20make%20calls%20by%20simply%20picking%20up%20the%20phone%20and%20dialing.%20She%20even%20made%20it%20so%20that%20when%20she%20dialed%20star%2C%20it%20would%20activate%20Siri%2C%20and%20she%20could%20direct%20it%20to%20call%20contacts%20by%20name%2C%20eliminating%20the%20need%20to%20memorize%20or%20look%20up%20a%20number.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225608%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Catherine%20Goetze%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e96b21cc993f9955d00436%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224128%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECatherine%20Goetze%20started%20Physical%20Phones%20after%20the%20positive%20reaction%20she%20got%20to%20the%20bluetooth%20rotary%20phone%20she%20made.%3Cp%3EYasara%20Gunawardena%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20summer%2C%20when%20she%20posted%20a%20video%20showing%20off%20the%20landline%20phone%20she'd%20been%20using%20for%20years%2C%20her%20comments%20were%20full%20of%20people%20saying%20they%20needed%20one%20too.%20That's%20how%20Goetze%20decided%20to%20start%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fphysicalphones%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPhysical%20Phones%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20makes%20and%20sells%20Bluetooth%20phones%20like%20the%20one%20she%20herself%20uses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20not%20realistic%20to%20throw%20your%20smartphone%20into%20a%20river%2C%26quot%3B%20Goetze%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Physical%20Phone%20says%2C%20'Look%2C%20keep%20your%20iPhone.%20But%20there%20are%20still%20ways%20that%20you%20can%20regain%20some%20level%20of%20balance%20and%20intentionality%20about%20achieving%20that%20balance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20phones%20are%20currently%20available%20for%20presale%20and%20expected%20to%20start%20shipping%20in%20November%20or%20December%2C%20but%20early%20signs%20are%20encouraging.%20Goetze%20said%20when%20they%20first%20launched%2C%20they%20generated%20%24118%2C000%20in%20pre-sales%20in%2072%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she%20thinks%20the%20orders%20are%20from%20a%20mix%20of%20millennials%20who%20are%20nostalgic%20for%20the%20landlines%20of%20their%20past%2C%20and%20zoomers%20who%20don't%20remember%20having%20a%20landline%20but%20are%20just%20as%20nostalgic%20and%20apt%20to%20romanticize%20that%20time%2C%20as%20evidenced%20by%20the%20resurgence%20in%20shows%20like%20%26quot%3BFriends%26quot%3B%20and%20Y2K%20fashion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoetze%20said%20she%20doesn't%20think%20most%20people%20want%20to%20live%20in%20a%20world%20without%20modern%20technology%2C%20but%20rather%20one%20where%20they%20are%20using%20that%20technology%20mindfully%2C%20rather%20than%20being%20used%20by%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-creating-own-versions-of-landlines-with-cellphones-2025-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1760355121000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e9631a5dbc4fd10daaa962%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-creating-own-versions-of-landlines-with-cellphones-2025-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Business%20Insider%20talked%20to%20three%20young%20adults%20who%20said%20creating%20a%20physical%20boundary%20around%20their%20phone%20improved%20their%20screen%20time%20and%20quality%20of%20life.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kvlamis%40businessinsider.com%20(Kelsey%20Vlamis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A47%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-creating-ow