%20wave%2C%20you%20might%20miss%20the%20rising%20tide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20at%20least%20some%20technologists%20and%20CEOs's%20dire%20predictions%2C%20AI%20will%20herald%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-ceo-warning-ai-could-eliminate-jobs-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20end%20of%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20we%20know%20it%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20for%20white%20collar%20employees.%20Yet%2C%20for%20now%2C%20AI%20isn't%20as%20likely%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoftware-engineer-not-afraid-ai-will-take-my-job-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esteal%20your%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20it%20is%20to%20reshape%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20couple%20of%20years%20will%20likely%20be%20bumpy%20as%20companies%20and%20employees%20figure%20out%20what%20AI%20can%20do%2C%20workplace%20observers%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20still%20very%2C%20very%20early%2C%26quot%3B%20Martha%20Gimbel%2C%20executive%20director%20and%20cofounder%20of%20the%20Budget%20Lab%20at%20Yale%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20She%20said%20the%20fears%20about%20AI%20as%20an%20imminent%20job%20killer%20%26quot%3Bspeaks%20to%20how%20much%20this%20debate%20has%2C%20frankly%2C%20gotten%20a%20little%20bit%20out%20of%20control.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecent%20Budget%20Lab%20research%20has%20found%20that%2C%20in%20the%20nearly%20three%20years%20since%20the%20release%20of%20ChatGPT%2C%20the%20overall%20labor%20market%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbudgetlab.yale.edu%2Fresearch%2Fevaluating-impact-ai-labor-market-current-state-affairs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehasn't%20experienced%20major%20disruptions%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That's%20because%20it%20often%20takes%20years%20%E2%80%94%20even%20decades%20%E2%80%94%20for%20people%20and%20businesses%20to%20adopt%20even%20breakthrough%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20not%20the%20case%20that%20ChatGPT%20is%20released%20and%20people%20know%20exactly%20what%20to%20do%20with%20their%20marketing%20departments%20the%20next%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20Gimbel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20because%20the%20technology%20feels%20%26quot%3Bso%20personal%20to%20so%20many%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20because%20it%20seemed%20to%20arrive%20overnight%20to%20many%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey%20are%20expecting%20the%20economic%20impacts%20to%20be%20as%20sudden%20and%20as%20jarring.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227f4c0eec-2212-4e11-957d-128179963942%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EJobs%20are%20changing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20absence%20of%20major%20disruptions%20doesn't%20mean%20your%20job%20looks%20the%20same%20as%20it%20used%20to.%20More%20than%20one%20in%20five%20US%20workers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2025%2F10%2F06%2Fabout-1-in-5-us-workers-now-use-ai-in-their-job-up-since-last-year%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euse%20AI%20to%20complete%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20least%20some%20of%20their%20work%2C%20the%20Pew%20Research%20Center%20found%20in%20a%20September%20survey.%20That's%20up%20from%2016%25%20about%20a%20year%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20those%20workers%20are%20likely%20in%20areas%20such%20as%20customer%20service%20or%20communications%2C%20which%20involve%20keyboard-heavy%20tasks%20where%20AI%20can%20excel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenerative%20AI%20can%20help%20communications%20staffers%20save%2026%25%20to%2036%25%20of%20their%20time%2C%20a%20recent%20study%20from%20Boston%20Consulting%20Group%20found.%20If%20companies%20change%20their%20processes%2C%20BCG%20estimates%20that%20GenAI%20can%20help%20increase%20the%20time%20savings%20of%20comms%20workers%20by%2047%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20could%20take%20a%20couple%20more%20years%20to%20determine%20whether%20GenAI%20will%20ultimately%20help%20comms%20teams%20save%20that%20much%20time%2C%20Russell%20Dubner%2C%20BCG's%20global%20chief%20communications%20officer%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EYet%2C%20in%20the%20meantime%2C%20he%20expects%20more%20companies%20to%20try%20to%20identify%20wider%2C%20department-level%20use%20in%20areas%20like%20communications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBCG's%20own%20communications%20team%20ran%20tests%20using%20AI%20and%20other%20tools%20to%20streamline%20repetitive%20tasks.%20That%20let%20the%20team%20free%20up%20capacity%20equivalent%20to%20about%2013%20full-time%20staffers%2C%20Dubner%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20time%20savings%20are%2C%20for%20now%2C%20how%20many%20employers%20appear%20to%20be%20looking%20at%20AI%20with%20questions%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BHave%20I%20created%20new%20capacity%20to%20do%20either%20a%20broader%20set%20of%20work%20or%20a%20higher%20value%20set%20of%20work%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClients%20he%20speaks%20with%20are%20less%20focused%20on%20cost%20savings%20and%20more%20on%20the%20fact%20that%20as%20much%20as%2080%25%20of%20corporate%20affairs%20roles%2C%20for%20example%2C%20can%20be%20augmented%20through%20GenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20they%20get%20those%20efficiencies%2C%26quot%3B%20Dubner%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228df2d6c1-f0b9-4be0-a952-a4752c04723f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAutomating%20tasks%20before%20jobs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20possible%20that%20AI%20will%20take%20over%20some%20jobs%20entirely%2C%20it's%20more%20likely%20AI%20will%20first%20absorb%20parts%20of%20jobs%2C%20Martin%20Ford%2C%20futurist%20and%20author%20of%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BRise%20of%20the%20Robots%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20that%20could%20mean%20fewer%20humans%20get%20hired%20overall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20company%20has%20two%20people%20doing%20the%20same%20work%2C%20and%20AI%20can%20take%20on%20half%20of%20those%20tasks%2C%20there%20will%20be%20less%20demand%20for%20people%2C%20Ford%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BManagement%2C%20at%20some%20point%2C%20is%20going%20to%20look%20at%20that%20and%20say%2C%20'Hey%2C%20you%20know%2C%20there's%20really%20only%20one%20job%20here%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-cloud-ceo-ai-automate-jobs-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI's%20impact%3C%2Fa%3E%20might%20be%20hard%20to%20discern%20across%20the%20economy%2C%20it's%20often%20more%20apparent%20within%20certain%20industries%20or%20regions%2C%20said%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EMona%20Mourshed%2C%20founding%20CEO%20of%20Generation%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20network%20focused%20on%20economic%20mobility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Generation's%20research%20found%20that%20for%20roles%20that%20appear%20%26quot%3BAI%20exposed%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20think%20areas%20like%20tech%2C%20customer%20service%2C%20and%20sales%20%E2%80%94%20entry-level%20job%20vacancy%20rates%20have%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20plunged%2020%25%20to%2040%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMourshed%20said%20that%20because%20AI%20advances%2C%20economic%20uncertainty%2C%20and%20changes%20in%20global%20supply%20chains%20are%20occurring%20simultaneously%2C%20it's%20difficult%20to%20know%20what's%20causing%20the%20decrease%20in%20job%20vacancies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2246ebf605-092a-4249-84e7-a5db737248d2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMixed%20signals%20on%20AI's%20impact%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20uncertainty%20surrounding%20AI's%20impact%20is%20reflected%20in%20disparate%20economic%20data.%20The%20Economic%20Innovation%20Group%2C%20in%20a%20recent%20analysis%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feig.org%2Fai-and-jobs-the-final-word%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeffect%20of%20AI%20on%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20found%20that%20workers%20%26quot%3Bhighly%20exposed%26quot%3B%20to%20AI%20are%20doing%20better%20in%20the%20labor%20market%20than%20those%20who%20are%20less%20so.%20The%20think%20tank%20said%20that%20workers%20more%20exposed%20to%20AI%20earn%20more%2C%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20have%20an%20undergraduate%20or%20graduate%20degree%2C%20and%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20be%20unemployed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20a%20recent%20Stanford%20study%20found%20that%20workers%20just%20starting%20their%20careers%20%E2%80%94%20those%20in%20their%20early%20to%20mid-20s%20%E2%80%94%20in%20fields%20susceptible%20to%20automation%20by%20AI%20have%20seen%20a%2013%25%20relative%20decrease%20in%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYale's%20Gimbel%20said%20that%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-to-do-if-need-job-frustrating-frozen-labor-market-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emany%20employers%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20%26quot%3Bslow%20to%20fire%2C%20slow%20to%20hire%26quot%3B%20recently%2C%20this%20has%20meant%20there%20are%20often%20fewer%20opportunities%20for%20graduates%2C%20as%20fewer%20established%20workers%20move%20around%20and%20create%20openings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20going%20to%20hit%20younger%20workers%20more%20than%20older%20workers%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMourshed%20said%20we'll%20likely%20need%20another%2012%20to%2018%20months%20to%20figure%20out%20AI's%20true%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20in%20the%20first%20stage%20of%20what%20will%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20could%20have%20lots%20of%20hypotheses%20about%20how%20it%20turns%20out%2C%20but%20fundamentally%2C%20no%20one%20knows%20yet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20AI's%20impact%20on%20your%20career%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Atparadis%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etparadis%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cu%3E.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimpact-ai-job-market-change-