3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20trio%20of%20economists%20said%20it%20won't%20replace%20key%20data%20that%20isn't%20being%20published%20during%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-a-us-government-shutdown-could-impact-your-next-flight-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Egovernment%20shutdown%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20shutdown%20continues%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-market-layoffs-firing-hiring-slowdown-recession-job-listings-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprivate%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20earnings%20calls%20offer%20useful%20clues%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20around%20company%20performance%20relative%20to%20expectations%2C%26quot%3B%20Gregory%20Daco%2C%20EY's%20chief%20economist%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20they're%20no%20substitute%20for%20broader%20and%20more%20consistent%20government%20data.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndependent%20economist%20Aaron%20Terrazas%20said%20earning%20calls%20can%20inform%20people%20about%20the%20direction%20of%20the%20economy%2C%20but%20they%20are%20not%20the%20same%20as%20government%20data%2C%20and%20people%20may%20have%20to%20read%20between%20the%20lines%20for%20what's%20being%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20a%20guessing%20game%20around%20how%20much%20of%20this%20is%20unique%20to%20the%20company%2C%20how%20much%20of%20this%20is%20unique%20to%20the%20sector%2C%20how%20much%20of%20this%20is%20the%20polish%20and%20spin%20that%20inevitably%20accompanies%20talking%20to%20investors%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20big%20federal%20data%20releases%20tend%20to%20be%20more%20open%20and%20straightforward.%20Terrazas%20said%20the%20government%20has%20vetted%20and%20transparent%20methodologies%20for%20its%20data%20%E2%80%94%20people%20can%20visit%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20website%20to%20find%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fopub%2Fhom%2Fces%2Fcalculation.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhole%20page%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20calculations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Hamrick%2C%20senior%20economic%20analyst%20at%20Bankrate%2C%20said%20bank%20CEOs%20are%20prone%20to%20saying%20in%20earnings%20calls%20that%20the%20consumer%20is%20doing%20well%2C%20but%20that%20has%20some%20caveats%3A%20consumers%20still%20need%20to%20buy%20necessities%2C%20and%20some%20are%20having%20a%20harder%20time%20than%20others.%20That%20means%20these%20calls%20may%20not%20capture%20the%20full%20picture%20of%20consumer%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEarnings%20calls%20will%20help%20to%20give%20us%20color%2C%20%26quot%3B%20Hamrick%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20it%20doesn't%20give%20us%20that%20fully%20fleshed%20out%20view%20that%20things%20like%20the%20CPI%20and%20the%20monthly%20employment%20situation%20read.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2268844cb5-a1cb-4989-b368-8340a6db444e%5C%22%3EA%20dearth%20of%20data%20while%20the%20government%20is%20shut%20down%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20has%20mostly%20folded%20up%20shop%20during%20the%20shutdown.%20Data%20reports%20haven't%20been%20released%20since%20October%201%2C%20and%20new%20data%20collection%20isn't%20happening.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgovernment-shutdown-jobs-report-bls-economic-data-job-seekers-fed-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejobs%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20arguably%20the%20most%20important%20economic%20data%20release%20of%20the%20month%20%E2%80%94%20wasn't%20published%20on%20its%20planned%20date%20of%20October%203.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20said%20on%20Friday%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fconsumer-price-index%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Econsumer%20price%20index%3C%2Fa%3E%20inflation%20report%20will%20be%20released%20on%20October%2024%20instead%20of%20its%20originally%20planned%20date%20of%20October%2015.%20The%20CPI%20report%20is%20especially%20important%20ahead%20of%20the%20Fed's%20next%20rate%20decision%20later%20this%20month.%20The%20September%20data%20is%20also%20needed%20for%20Social%20Security's%20annual%20cost-of-living%20adjustment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrivate%20data%20has%20helped%20fill%20in%20some%20of%20the%20gaps%20in%20understanding%20the%20state%20of%20the%20job%20market%20in%20September%2C%20but%20the%20findings%20were%20mixed.%20ADP's%20analysis%20showed%20a%20loss%20of%2032%2C000%20private-sector%20jobs%2C%20while%20Revelio%20Labs%20found%20the%20US%20added%2060%2C000%20nonfarm%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20all%20highly%20reliant%20on%20information%20about%20the%20performance%20of%20the%20US%20economy%2C%20and%20the%20federal%20data%20is%20the%20gold%20standard%20measuring%20that%20performance%2C%26quot%3B%20Hamrick%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics'%20jobs%20report%20is%20closely%20watched%20to%20see%20how%20the%20workforce%20is%20evolving.%20It%20helps%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20make%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-cuts-interest-rates-decision-jerome-powell-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterest%20rate%20decisions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20helps%20economists%20understand%20changes%20to%20the%20labor%20force%2C%20wage%20growth%2C%20and%20unemployment%2C%20and%20helps%20job%20seekers%20identify%20industries%20that%20are%20hiring%20more%20than%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20air%20traffic%20control%20for%20the%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20Daco%20said.%20%26quot%3BPlanes%20can't%20land%20safely%20without%20FAA%20staff%20%E2%80%94%20and%20businesses%20can't%20make%20sound%20investment%20or%20hiring%20decisions%20in%20a%20data%20fog.%20Consumers%2C%20too%2C%20lose%20confidence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3